[title size="2"]Aida B. Tomines, At-Large Governor[/title]

<span style="color: #000000;">Aida B. Tomines was elected to the EAA Board of Governors in November 2013 as At-Large Governor representing MOU's 1, 19, 20, and 21.</span>

<span style="color: #000000;">Employed by the City of Los Angeles for over twenty-five years, Governor Tomines started her public service in the City Controller's Office Demand Audit Division as an Accountant and later promoted to Senior Accountant.</span>

<span style="color: #000000;">In 1998, Governor Tomines was a Senior Representative and Unit Council Member for MOU 1Â andÂ MOU 20. In the fall of 2003, she would be electedÂ EAA Governor representing MOU 20. As acting EAA Governor from 2004 to 2011, Aida B.Â Tomines was actively involved and instrumental in many serious issues to protect EAA members careers, benefits, and rights in the workplace.</span>

<span style="color: #000000;">Dedicated to returning Integrity, Accountability, and Transparency to EAA Board of Governors and to your Union, Governor Tomines was elected At- Large Governor in the Fall of 2013.</span>
[/two_third]

